newsitem.title: USA: Nebraska fed cattle market quiet, no trade-private.
newsitem.headline: Nebraska fed cattle market quiet, no trade-private.

text.p: The Nebraska feedlot cattle market was quiet, with no reported sales, market sources said.

Bids were light at $101.00-$102.00 per cwt on a dressed basis and passed by owners pricing cattle at $104.00, the sources said. Cattle were priced $64.00 to $65.00 on a live basis, with no reported bids.
The bulk of last week's cattle sales were at $103.00/dressed and $64.00/live.
The showlist was estimated near 87,000 head, up 2,000 from last week, several market sources said.
